verses.verse: To the chief <S%H5329>Musician<s%> on <S%H5058>Neginoth,<s%> A <S%H4210>Psalm<s%> or <S%H7892>Song<s%> of <S%H623>Asaph.<s%> In <S%H3063>Judah<s%> is <S%H430>God<s%> <S%H3045>known:<s%> his <S%H8034>name<s%> is <S%H1419>great<s%> in <S%H3478>Israel.<s%>
In <S%H8004>Salem<s%> also <S%H1961>is<s%> his <S%H5520>tabernacle,<s%> and his dwelling <S%H4585>place<s%> in <S%H6726>Zion.<s%>
There <S%H8033><s%> <S%H7665>broke<s%> he the <S%H7565>arrows<s%> of the <S%H7198>bow,<s%> the <S%H4043>shield,<s%> and the <S%H2719>sword,<s%> and the <S%H4421>battle.<s%> <S%H5542>Selah.<s%>
Thou <S%H859><s%> art more <S%H215>glorious<s%> and <S%H117>excellent<s%> than the <S%H4480>mountains<s%> <S%H2042><s%> of <S%H2964>prey.<s%>

The <S%H47>stouthearted<s%> <S%H3820><s%> are <S%H7997>spoiled,<s%> they have <S%H5123>slept<s%> their <S%H8142>sleep:<s%> and <S%H3808>none<s%> <S%H3605><s%> of the <S%H376>men<s%> of <S%H2428>might<s%> have <S%H4672>found<s%> their <S%H3027>hands.<s%>
At thy <S%H4480>rebuke,<s%> <S%H1606><s%> O <S%H430>God<s%> of <S%H3290>Jacob,<s%> both the <S%H7393>chariot<s%> and <S%H5483>horse<s%> are cast into a dead <S%H7290>sleep.<s%>

Thou, <S%H859><s%> even <S%H859>thou,<s%> art to be <S%H3372>feared:<s%> and <S%H4310>who<s%> may <S%H5975>stand<s%> in thy <S%H6440>sight<s%> when <S%H4480>once<s%> <S%H227><s%> thou art <S%H639>angry?<s%>
Thou didst cause <S%H1779>judgment<s%> to be <S%H8085>heard<s%> <S%H4480>from<s%> <S%H8064>heaven;<s%> the <S%H776>earth<s%> <S%H3372>feared,<s%> and was <S%H8252>still,<s%>
When <S%H430>God<s%> <S%H6965>arose<s%> to <S%H4941>judgment,<s%> to <S%H3467>save<s%> <S%H3605>all<s%> the <S%H6035>meek<s%> of the <S%H776>earth.<s%> <S%H5542>Selah.<s%>
Surely <S%H3588><s%> the <S%H2534>wrath<s%> of <S%H120>man<s%> shall <S%H3034>praise<s%> thee: the <S%H7611>remainder<s%> of <S%H2534>wrath<s%> shalt thou <S%H2296>restrain.<s%>

Vow, <S%H5087><s%> and <S%H7999>pay<s%> unto the <S%H3068>LORD<s%> your <S%H430>God:<s%> let <S%H3605>all<s%> that be round <S%H5439>about<s%> him <S%H2986>bring<s%> <S%H7862>presents<s%> unto him that ought to be <S%H4172>feared.<s%>
He shall cut <S%H1219>off<s%> the <S%H7307>spirit<s%> of <S%H5057>princes:<s%> he is <S%H3372>terrible<s%> to the <S%H4428>kings<s%> of the <S%H776>earth.<s%>
